article.description: Darius Jones-Gibson scored 10 of his 15 points in the first half and Samford cruised past crosstown-foe Miles College 104-76 Tuesday night.
article.headline: Samford beats crosstown foe Miles 104-76
article.story: BIRMINGHAM, Ala. -- Darius Jones-Gibson scored 10 of his 15 points in the first half and Samford cruised past crosstown-foe Miles College 104-76 Tuesday night. Jones-Gibson scored the first four points of the game as Samford jumped out to a 15-1 lead. Miles, an NCAA Division II member, went scoreless again for nearly four minutes and trailed 33-10 with seven minutes left in the half. Samford doubled up Miles at halftime, 54-27, in its final non-conference outing of the season. Matt Rose led Samford (9-4) with 16 points, nine coming in the second half. Marcus Johnson made three of Samford's 11 3-pointers and scored 13 points with seven assists. Iman Johnson had 10 points and nine rebounds as the Bulldogs outrebounded Miles 50-39. Maiscei Grier made three 3-pointers and scored 18 points for Miles, which turned it over 20 times in its third straight loss.
